law.text:
The president of the College shall:
Report directly to the Board of Trustees;
Recommend the appointment by the Board of Trustees of qualified faculty members and other employees necessary for the efficient administration of the College;
Recommend the discharge of employees for good cause, provided that any employee with tenure shall be given reasonable notice of the grounds for dismissal and an opportunity to be heard;
Be responsible for the conduct of the College and for the administration and supervision of its departments; and
Attend all meetings of the Board of Trustees, except those involving the position of president.
